{
  "texts": [
    "The 'naïve' assumption is that the features are conditionally independent, simplifying the modeling process and making it computationally efficient.",
    "The key advantages of this model involve the speed, and suitability for high-dimensional data.",
    "However, its naïve independence assumption may not hold in complex real-world datasets, potentially affecting accuracy.",
    "It also struggles with rare events and might require extensive data preprocessing (Yang et al. 2019).",
    "Unsupervised learning deals with unlabeled data."
  ]
}